Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Phyloseptin-S1 (natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; UCLL1)
Sequence Information.Source: The gliding tree frog,Agalychnis spurrelli, Central America

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals this sequence is most similar (95%) toPhylloseptin-1. Note that the last residue G in Phyloseptin-S1 is converted to amide in Phylloseptin-1 from a different species. Thus, these two peptides are essentially the same as can be seen from the similar activity spectrum.Activity: Active against E. coli ATCC 25922 (MIC 70 uM) and S. aureus ATCC 25923 (MIC 6.3 uM).
Literature Information.Author: Proaño-Bolaños C, Blasco-Zúñiga A, Almeida JR, Wang L,  Llumiquinga MA, Rivera M, Zhou M, Chen T, Shaw C. 2019
Literature Information.Title: Unravelling the Skin Secretion Peptides of the Gliding Leaf Frog, Agalychnis spurrelli (Hylidae)
